docs.abstract: The  administration will propose that federal agencies be allowed to disregard climate change when  assessing the environmental effects of  major  projects.
docs.snippet: The  administration will propose that federal agencies be allowed to disregard climate change when  assessing the environmental effects of  major  projects.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal agencies would no longer have to take climate change into account when they assess the environmental impacts of highways, pipelines and other major infrastructure projects, according to a Trump administration plan that would weaken the nation’s benchmark environmental law.

headline.main: Trump Rule Would Exclude Climate Change in Infrastructure Planning
headline.print_headline: Trump Moves to Weaken Environmental Shield

docs.abstract: Attacks have been traditionally underreported, but fighting the scourge in hate crimes begins with better data, experts say.
docs.snippet: Attacks have been traditionally underreported, but fighting the scourge in hate crimes begins with better data, experts say.
docs.lead_paragraph: When slurs were spray-painted on a kosher market in West Los Angeles, it was classified by law enforcement as an anti-Semitic hate crime. But when a swastika was carved into a park picnic table or spray-painted on a stop sign, it was classified as an anti-religious hate crime.

headline.main: ‘A Different Era’: Anti-Semitic Crimes, and Efforts to Track Them, Climb
headline.print_headline: Scrutiny Reveals a Rise in Anti-Semitic Crimes

docs.abstract: A day after a deceptively edited video of him spread on social media, Joseph R. Biden Jr. cautioned that the Democratic nominee would be vulnerable to false information in the general election.
docs.snippet: A day after a deceptively edited video of him spread on social media, Joseph R. Biden Jr. cautioned that the Democratic nominee would be vulnerable to false information in the general election.
docs.lead_paragraph: ANAMOSA, Iowa — As the Democratic presidential candidates fanned out across Iowa and New Hampshire on Thursday to address voters still scarred by President Trump’s victory in the 2016 election, Joseph R. Biden Jr. argued that any Democratic nominee would be vulnerable to baseless criticism and disinformation in the general election.

headline.main: Biden Warns About Disinformation After Misleading Video
headline.print_headline: Biden Warns Fellow Candidates of Disinformation in 2020 ‘Mosh Pit’
